        model: 'Model answer: First, JWST operates 1.5 million kilometres from Earth at the L2 point, whereas Hubble orbits only around 600 kilometres above the surface. Second, JWST detects infrared light, which allows it to observe galaxies formed much earlier in the universe\'s history than Hubble could reach.'
