        guidance: 'Mark scheme: 1 mark for identifying that Arctic amplification refers to the Arctic warming faster than the rest of the planet (approximately four times faster). 1 mark for explaining the albedo/feedback loop mechanism: white ice reflects sunlight; as ice melts it is replaced by darker water that absorbs more heat; this causes further warming and more melting. Both elements needed for full marks.',
        model: 'Model answer: Arctic amplification is the phenomenon by which the Arctic warms approximately four times faster than the rest of the planet. It is caused by a feedback loop involving sea ice: white ice reflects sunlight (albedo), but as warming melts the ice, it is replaced by darker ocean water that absorbs much more heat, causing further warming and further ice loss.'
